==Deaths==
*  [[79]] &amp;ndash; [[Pliny the Elder]], Roman writer and [[Natural history|naturalist]] (b. 23)
*[[1042]] &amp;ndash; [[Michael V Kalaphates]], [[Byzantine Emperor]] (b. 1015)
*[[1103]] &amp;ndash; King [[Magnus III of Norway]] (b. 1073)
*[[1217]] &amp;ndash; [[Eustace the Monk]], French mercenary and pirate (b. c.1170)
*[[1540]] &amp;ndash; [[Girolamo Francesco Maria Mazzola]], Italian painter (b. 1503)
*[[1542]] &amp;ndash; [[Gasparo Contarini]], Italian diplomat and cardinal (b. 1483)
*[[1572]] &amp;ndash; Victims of the [[St. Bartholomew's Day Massacre]]:
:*                [[Gaspard de Coligny]], French [[Huguenot]] leader (b. 1519)
:*                [[Petrus Ramus|Pierre de la Ramée]], French humanist (b. 1515)
:*                [[Charles de Téligny]], French Huguenot soldier (b. c.1535)
*[[1595]] &amp;ndash; [[Thomas Digges]], English astronomer (b. 1546)
*[[1647]] &amp;ndash; [[Nicholas Stone]], English sculptor and architect (b. 1586)
*[[1664]] &amp;ndash; [[Maria Cunitz]], Silesian astronomer (b. c.1610)
*[[1679]] &amp;ndash; [[Jean François Paul de Gondi]], French cardinal and agitator (b. 1614)
*[[1680]] &amp;ndash; [[Thomas Blood]], Irish-born thief of the British crown jewels (b. 1618)
*[[1683]] &amp;ndash; [[John Owen (theologian)|John Owen]], English non-conformist theologian (b. 1616)
*[[1759]] &amp;ndash; [[Ewald Christian von Kleist]], German poet (b. 1715)
*[[1779]] &amp;ndash; Saint [[Cosmas of Aetolia]], Greek Orthodox martyr (b. 1714)
*[[1798]] &amp;ndash; [[Thomas Alcock (1709-1798)|Thomas Alcock]], English clergyman (b. 1709)
*[[1818]] &amp;ndash; [[James Carr (Massachusetts politician)|James Carr]], U.S. Congressman (b. 1777)
*[[1831]] &amp;ndash; [[August von Gneisenau]], Prussian field marshal (b. 1760)
*[[1832]] &amp;ndash; [[Nicolas Léonard Sadi Carnot]], French mathematician (b. 1796)
*[[1841]] &amp;ndash; [[Theodore Edward Hook]], English author (b. 1788)
*  1841   &amp;ndash; [[John Ordronaux (privateer)|John Ordronaux]], [[privateer]] of the [[War of 1812]] (b. 1778)
*[[1888]] &amp;ndash; [[Rudolf Clausius]], German physicist (b. 1822)
*[[1895]] &amp;ndash; [[Albert F. Mummery]], British mountaineer (b. 1855)
*[[1921]] &amp;ndash; [[Nikolay Gumilyov]], Russian poet (b. 1886)
*[[1930]] &amp;ndash; [[Tom Norman]], English freak showman (b. 1860)
*[[1940]] &amp;ndash; [[Paul Gottlieb Nipkow]], German television pioneer (b. 1860)
*[[1943]] &amp;ndash; [[Simone Weil]], French philosopher and social activist (b. 1909)
*  1943   &amp;ndash; [[Antonio Alice]], Argentine portrait painter (b. 1886)
*[[1945]] &amp;ndash; [[Midori Naka]], Japanese actress, survivor of the Hiroshima atomic bombing, died of radiation poisoning (b. 1909)
*[[1946]] &amp;ndash; [[James Clark McReynolds]], U.S. Supreme Court justice (b. 1862)
*[[1954]] &amp;ndash; [[Getúlio Vargas]], [[President of Brazil]] (b. 1882)
*[[1956]] &amp;ndash; [[Kenji Mizoguchi]], Japanese film director (b. 1898)
*[[1958]] &amp;ndash; [[Paul Henry (painter)|Paul Henry]], Northern Irish artist (b. 1876)
*[[1961]] &amp;ndash; [[Günter Litfin]], the first person to be [[Deaths at the Berlin Wall|shot at the Berlin Wall]]
*[[1967]] &amp;ndash; [[Henry J. Kaiser]], American industrialist (b. 1882)
*  1967   &amp;ndash; [[Lam Bun]], Hong Kong radio commentator (murdered) (b. 1930)
*[[1974]] &amp;ndash; [[Alexander de Seversky]], Russian-American aviation pioneer  (b. 1894)
*[[1977]] &amp;ndash; [[Buddy O'Connor]], Canadian ice hockey player (b. 1916)
*[[1978]] &amp;ndash; [[Louis Prima]], American band leader (b. 1910)
*[[1979]] &amp;ndash; [[Hanna Reitsch]], German [[test pilot]] (b. 1912)
*  1979   &amp;ndash; [[Sampson Sievers]], Russian Orthodox Christian monk and wonder-worker (b. 1898)
*[[1980]] &amp;ndash; [[Yootha Joyce]], British actress (b. 1927)
*[[1982]] &amp;ndash; [[Félix-Antoine Savard]], French Canadian catholic priest and novelist (b. 1896)
*[[1983]] &amp;ndash; [[Scott Nearing]], American writer, educator and activist (b. 1883)
*[[1985]] &amp;ndash; [[Paul Creston]], American composer (b. 1906)
*[[1987]] &amp;ndash; [[Malcolm Kirk]], English wrestler (b. 1936)
*[[1990]] &amp;ndash; [[Sergei Dovlatov]], Russian writer (b. 1941)
*  1990   &amp;ndash; [[Gailli AbedElrhman]], Sudanese writer (b. 1931)
*[[1991]] &amp;ndash; [[Bernard Castro]], Italian inventor (b. 1904)
*[[1995]] &amp;ndash; [[Alfred Eisenstaedt]], German-born photographer (b. 1898)
*[[1997]] &amp;ndash; [[Werner Abrolat]], German actor (b. 1924)
*[[1998]] &amp;ndash; [[E.G. Marshall]], American actor (b. 1910)
*[[1999]] &amp;ndash; [[Alexandre Lagoya]], Greek-Italian classical guitarist (b. 1929)
*[[2000]] &amp;ndash; [[Andy Hug]], Swiss karateka and kickbox champion (b. 1964)
*[[2001]] &amp;ndash; [[Jane Greer]], American actress (b. 1924)
*[[2002]] &amp;ndash; [[Nikolay Guryanov]] Russian Orthodox Christian mystic and priest (b. 1909)
*[[2003]] &amp;ndash; Sir [[Wilfred Thesiger]], British explorer (b. 1910)
*[[2004]] &amp;ndash; [[Elisabeth Kübler-Ross]], Swiss-born psychiatrist (b. 1926)
*[[2005]] &amp;ndash; [[Kaleth Morales]], Colombian Vallenato singer (b. 1984)
*  2005   &amp;ndash; [[Kalin Twins|Harold &quot;Hal&quot; Kalin]], American singer (The Kalin Twins) (b. 1934)
*[[2006]] &amp;ndash; [[Léopold Simoneau]], French Canadian tenor (b. 1916)
*  2006   &amp;ndash; [[Cristian Nemescu]], Romanian film director (b. 1979)
*  2006   &amp;ndash; [[Rocco Petrone]], American engineer (b. 1926)
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; [[Andrée P. Boucher]], Mayor of [[Quebec City]] (b. 1937)
*  2007   &amp;ndash; [[Aaron Russo]], American film producer and director (b. 1943)
